						               													<description>The alarm clock rings and you're already got up on the wrong side of the bed. Daily routines can sometimes put the brakes on your best days.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Burnt toast, slip in the shower and spilled coffee will slow you down in your race to start the day. Overcome all the obstacles, be the first to discard all your cards and win before the bus leaves without you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Preparation&amp;#10;Shuffle all the cards and deal seven cards to each player. Turn over the top card from the deck to make the discard pile. The person who gets up earliest starts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How the game works&amp;#10;When it is your turn, play a card from your hand on the last card played or, if you can't, draw a card from the deck. Then the turn passes to the player on your left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To play a card from your hand, it must match the condition on the back of the top card of the deck (+,-,=...).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you can't play a card from your hand because you don't have a card that meets the condition, draw a card from the deck. This changes the condition for the next player, and the turn then passes to the person on your left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are also some special cards that can be played at any time regardless of the condition shown on the top card (burnt toast, dropped soap, broken alarm clock...).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when a player gets rid of all the of cards in their hand. Now you're ready to get on the bus and start your day in the best way!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
